main event: A disc-shaped unidentified flying object was spotted over Youngstown, Ohio on March 6, 1967.
interesting points: The object was described as silvery, disc-shaped, and approximately 30 feet in diameter, with no visible means of propulsion.
The witness, Mr. John Doe, was able to obtain a photograph of the object before it accelerated and departed the area at a high rate of speed.
Multiple witnesses reported similar sightings of unidentified flying objects in the Youngstown area around this time period.
The photographs taken by Mr. Doe were forwarded to Project Blue Book for analysis.
One of the photographs shows a blurry, shadowy object in the sky above a winter landscape with bare trees.
photographs: yes, the report includes several photographs of the UFO
